headline: Trump names Bowman as Fed's top bank cop, signaling shift in regulatory stance
summary: Michelle Bowman would likely take oversight of the nation’s largest banks in a new direction as the Trump administration makes it clear it wants to lift constraints on lenders and revisit a regulatory framework put in place after the 2008 financial crisis.
